1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,649
He wanted improvements.

2
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:06,690
All day, this third salesman gave me his ideas for getting new business,

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:14,450
providing better service to customers, reducing wasted time, revising the compensation plan to give more incentive,

4
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:17,889
all so that he and the company would make more.

5
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:22,369
He had mapped out a new advertising campaign he had been thinking about.

6
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:29,730
When I left him, his parting remark was, I sure appreciate the chance to tell someone about some of my ideas.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,730
We've got a good outfit, but I believe we can make it better.

8
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:37,730
My recommendation, of course, was for the third man.

9
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:43,170
It was a recommendation that coincided perfectly with the feelings of the company president.

10
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:54,450
Believe in expansion, efficiency, new products, new processes, better schools, increased prosperity, Believe in and push for progress,

11
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,129
and you'll be a leader.

12
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:06,369
As a youngster, I had an opportunity to see how the different thinking of two leaders can make an amazing difference in the performance of followers.

13
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:09,810
I attended a country elementary school.

14
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:16,530
Eight grades, one teacher, and 40 children all jammed together inside four brick walls.

15
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:19,490
A new teacher was always a big deal.

16
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:26,849
Led by the big boys, the seventh and eighth graders, the pupils set out to see how much they could get away with.

17
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:30,050
One year there was little more than chaos.

18
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:36,930
Every day there were dozens of the usual school pranks, wars of spitballs and paper airplanes.

19
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:43,329
Then there were the major incidents, such as locking the teacher outside the school for half a day at a time,

20
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:48,770
or on another occasion the opposite, barricading her within the building for hours.

21
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:54,129
Another day, each boy in the upper grades brought his dog into the schoolroom.

22
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:58,210
Let me add that these children were not delinquents.

23
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:03,089
Stealing, physical violence, and deliberate harm were not their objectives.

24
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:11,889
They were healthy kids, conditioned by vigorous rural living, and needing an outlet for their tremendous pent-up energies and ingenuities.

25
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:17,649
Well, the teacher somehow managed to stay with the school until the end of that year.

26
00:02:17,839 --> 00:02:22,369
To no one's surprise, there was a new teacher the following September.

27
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:27,730
The new teacher extracted strikingly different performance from the children.

28
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:31,729
She appealed to their personal pride and sense of respect.

29
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,450
She encouraged them to develop judgment.

30
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:41,410
Each child was assigned a specific responsibility, like washing blackboards or cleaning erasers,

31
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:44,609
or practicing paper grading for the younger grades.

32
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:51,490
The new teacher found creative ways to use the energy that had been so misdirected a few months before.

33
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:55,889
Her educational program was centered on building character.

34
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:02,369
Why did the children act like young devils one year and like young angels the next?

35
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:05,410
The difference was the leader, their teacher.

36
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:11,089
In all honesty, we cannot blame the kids for playing pranks an entire school year.

37
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,369
In each instance, the teacher set the pace.

38
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:19,810
The first teacher, deep down, didn't care whether the children made progress.

39
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,129
She set no goals for the children.

40
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,810
She didn't encourage them.

41
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,000
She couldn't control her temper.
